# Build Workflow

The extension has three separate build targets. Which ones you need depends on what files changed.

## After changing webview TypeScript (`src/webviews/erd-v2-split/*.ts`)

Run **both**:

```bash
npm run build:erd     # compiles TS → dist/erd-v2.js
npm run build:ext     # copies CSS/HTML → dist/webview-static/
```

Or just: `npm run build`

## After changing webview CSS or HTML (`src/webviews/erd-v2-split/*.css`, `*.html`)

```bash
npm run build:ext     # copies static files to dist/webview-static/
```

`build:erd` alone does NOT copy CSS/HTML — only `build:ext` does (via `esbuild.config.js` lines 26-32).

## After changing extension TypeScript (`src/**/*.ts` excluding `erd-v2-split/`)

```bash
npm run build:ext     # bundles extension → dist/extension.js
```

## Full build (before VSIX packaging or when unsure)

```bash
npm run build         # runs build:ext + build:erd
```

## Key detail

The webview reads CSS/HTML from `dist/webview-static/` (not from `src/`). If that directory exists, it takes priority over the source files. Always ensure it's up to date after CSS/HTML changes.
